    <name>
      <text>7.3.26 (Write sim. eqns. with matrices)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Write the following system of linear equations as a matrix equation.
\[
\begin{align*}
&{@a1@}x_1 + {@a2@}x_2 + {@a3@}x_3 = {@b1@}
\\
&{@a4@}x_1 + {@a5@}x_2 + {@a6@}x_3 = {@b2@}
\\
&{@a7@}x_1 + {@a8@}x_2 + {@a9@}x_3 = {@b3@}
\end{align*}
\]</p>

<ul style="list-style-type:none;">
<li>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] \(\begin{bmatrix}
x_1
\\
x_2
\\
x_3
\end{bmatrix} = \)[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]
</li>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We can use matrices to write this equation in the form \(A \mathbf{x} = \mathbf{b}\).  So the coefficients of each \(x_i\) are the entries of the matrix \(A\) and the entries of the vector \(\mathbf{b}\) are the values on the right hand side of the equals sign. So we have 
\[
{@ta1@} \begin{bmatrix}
x_1
\\
x_2
\\
x_3
\end{bmatrix} = {@ta2@}.
\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
